1 olive oil
1 onion
1 carrot
1 cucumber
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 tbs soy sauce
1 packet teriyaki sauce
1 tsp brown sugar
1 packet pork mince
1 packet Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 bag coriander

• Finely chop brown onion. Grate carrot. Thinly slice cucumber into half-moons.
• In a medium bowl, combine a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Add slaw mix and cucumber. Set aside.
• In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, 1/2 the soy sauce and a splash of water. Set aside.
• In a second small bowl, combine teriyaki sauce, brown sugar, remaining soy sauce and a splash of water.

• Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Cook onion and carrot until starting to soften, 2-3 minutes.
• Add pork mince and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned,3-4 minutes.
• Add ginger & lemongrass paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add teriyaki sauce mixture, then stir to combine and simmer until slightly reduced, 1 minute.

• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.
• Season slaw and toss to combine.

• Top tortillas with teriyaki pork and slaw.
• Spoon over soy mayo. Sprinkle with crispy shallots.
• Tear over coriander to serve.